Pascal solved it by looking forward. What happens next? Player A gets the n=
ext point, he wins. Player B gets the next point, it=E2=80=99s tied at 2-2 =
and the odds are back to 50/50. So Player A has a 75% chance of winning: 50=
% of winning immediately + (50% * 50%) in the tied scenario. Player B has a=
 25% chance of winning. They should actually split the pot 3:1.=C2=A0
Pascal and Fermat wrote to each other at the height of the Scientific Revol=
