0;"><span>Pascal solved it by looking </span><em>forward.</em><span> What h=
appens next? Player A gets the next point, he wins. Player B gets the next =
point, it&#8217;s tied at 2-2 and the odds are back to 50/50. So Player A h=
as a 75% chance of winning: 50% of winning immediately + (50% * 50%) in the=
 tied scenario. Player B has a 25% chance of winning. They should actually =
